event.title: 1870, Dr. Horace Greeley Smith and his wife filed

data.event: In 1870, Dr. Horace Greeley Smith and his wife filed a homestead claim at the site of present-day Exeter.

event.title: fall of 1871, the Burlington and Missouri was completed

data.event: In the fall of 1871, the Burlington and Missouri was completed through Fillmore County.

event.title: 1878, two large grain elevators were built

data.event: In 1878, two large grain elevators were built and a number of businesses opened; the town's first newspaper, the Enterprise, was established in that year.
In 1878, two large grain elevators were built and a number of businesses opened; the town's first newspaper, the Enterprise, was established in that year.
In 1879, the town was incorporated; by that time, it had sixteen businesses.
